com.crudetech.junit.feature

Interface Equivalent.Factory<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    Enclosing class:
    Equivalent<T>

    public static interface Equivalent.Factory<T>
    Factory that is used by the Equivalent fixture to construct the objects needed for the tests.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      T createItem()
      When implemented, each call creates a unique item that is equal to other instances created by this method before.
      List<T> createOtherItems()
      When implemented, it returns a set of objects that are not equal to the ones created by createItem().

    • Method Detail

      • createItem

        T createItem()
        When implemented, each call creates a unique item that is equal to other instances created by this method before.
        Returns:
        As unique instance as described.

      • createOtherItems

        List<T> createOtherItems()
        When implemented, it returns a set of objects that are not equal to the ones created by createItem().

        When the class under test consist has several properties that are compared in it Object.equals(Object) method, this method will return a set of object that are permutations of these properties.

        Returns:
        A list of instances as described.
